---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Japan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/japan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
  { title: 'Taiwan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/taiwan' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'japanFit', header: 'Japan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$420-580/mo', japanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$480-680/mo', japanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$380-520/mo', japanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$360-500/mo', japanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Japanese NHI', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '~10% income', japanFit: 'Full Access' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$380-580', annual: '$4,560-6,960' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$520-750', annual: '$6,240-9,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$700-1,000', annual: '$8,400-12,000' },
  { category: 'Japanese National Health Insurance', monthly: '~10% income', annual: 'Income-based' },
  { category: 'Japanese Kokumin Nenkin (Pension)', monthly: '¥16,980', annual: '¥203,760' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Japan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Japan. National Health Insurance, Tokyo hospitals, visa options, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Japan"
  subheadline="Japan offers exceptional healthcare, safety, and culture—with one of the world's best national health systems available to residents."
  heroImage="/images/countries/japan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Japan</h2>
  <p>
    Japan combines ancient culture with cutting-edge modernity, offering seniors exceptional safety, world-class healthcare, efficient transportation, and a society that deeply respects elders. The country has the world's longest life expectancy for a reason.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tokyo provides endless cultural activities and the best medical facilities. Kyoto offers traditional atmosphere with excellent infrastructure. Okinawa attracts retirees with its subtropical climate and Blue Zone longevity. Smaller cities like Fukuoka and Sendai provide lower costs with good healthcare access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; ranked #1 or #2 globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Japanese essential; limited English outside tourist areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ¥200,000-350,000/month ($1,400-2,500) outside Tokyo</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> One of the safest countries globally</li>
      <li><strong>Public Transport:</strong> Exceptional; Shinkansen connects major cities</li>
      <li><strong>Culture:</strong> Respectful society with strong emphasis on elder care</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Japan's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Japan's National Health Insurance (NHI) system is mandatory for all residents and provides comprehensive coverage. Patients pay 30% of costs (10% for those 75+), with the government covering the rest. Monthly premiums are income-based.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare quality is exceptional. Japan has the highest number of MRI machines per capita, short wait times for most procedures, and doctors who typically spend more time with patients than in Western countries. Major hospitals in Tokyo, Osaka, and other cities have international departments with English support.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Language Consideration</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Japanese is essential for navigating healthcare outside major cities. While international hospitals exist in Tokyo and Osaka, most clinics and smaller hospitals operate primarily in Japanese. Consider learning basic Japanese or arranging for translation services.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Japan doesn't have a traditional retirement visa, but several pathways exist for seniors:
  </p>

  <h3>Designated Activities Visa (Retirement)</h3>
  <p>
    Available to retirees with significant assets (typically ¥30M+) and stable income. Requires proof of comprehensive health insurance and financial self-sufficiency. Valid 1 year, renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor/Business Manager Visa</h3>
  <p>
    If you start a small business or investment in Japan, you can obtain residency. Investment of ¥5M+ or employing 2+ Japanese nationals required.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Term Resident Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with Japanese ancestry or long-standing ties to Japan. More flexible requirements but specific eligibility criteria.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Japan requires all residents to enroll in either National Health Insurance (NHI) or employee health insurance:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive international insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>After residency:</strong> Must enroll in NHI within 14 days of registration</li>
    <li><strong>NHI coverage:</strong> 70% of costs covered (90% for 75+)</li>
    <li><strong>International backup:</strong> Many expats maintain international insurance for evacuation and flexibility</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Dual Coverage Strategy</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Many senior expats in Japan maintain both NHI (for local care and legal compliance) and international insurance (for evacuation, home country visits, and English-language support). This provides comprehensive protection while meeting Japanese requirements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors moving to Japan, these international providers offer strong coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Japan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Japanese hospital network, 24/7 English support</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), excellent international evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good value, strong Asian network</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> Competitive pricing for Japan coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Japan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Japan are influenced by the excellent but mandatory NHI system:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHI primary:</strong> Use Japanese NHI as primary; international as supplement</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> With NHI covering most care, you can choose high-deductible international plans</li>
    <li><strong>Japan exclusion:</strong> Some expats exclude Japan from international coverage once enrolled in NHI</li>
    <li><strong>Okinawa/rural:</strong> Living outside Tokyo significantly reduces overall costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving to Kyoto with $5,000/month income. Wants comprehensive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa application, then enroll in Japanese NHI. Keep Cigna for evacuation and US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NHI ~¥50,000/month + Cigna (Japan excluded) ~$350/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring to Okinawa for the climate and Blue Zone lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global initially, transition to NHI after residency established.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$1,100/month combined initially, dropping to NHI (~¥80,000/month combined) after transition.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Japanese Heritage, 74</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Returning to Japan with spouse. Has some health history.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Long-term resident visa available. Immediate NHI enrollment. International insurance for home country visits only.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NHI income-based + limited international coverage ~$200/month.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Japanese really necessary for healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In Tokyo and Osaka, international hospitals with English-speaking staff exist. However, most neighborhood clinics and hospitals operate in Japanese. For the best experience, basic Japanese is highly recommended, or arrange for a medical interpreter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Japan's NHI compare to Western systems?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Japan's NHI is often considered the world's best. Wait times are minimal, doctor access is easy, and quality is exceptional. The 30% co-pay (10% for 75+) is manageable, and there are caps on annual out-of-pocket costs. Prescription drugs are affordable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Japan without significant wealth?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Japan's retirement visa typically requires substantial assets. However, other pathways exist: starting a small business, marriage to a Japanese national, or ancestral connections. Some retirees use long-stay tourist visas (90 days) with periodic exits, though this isn't a long-term solution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about pre-existing conditions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Japanese NHI covers pre-existing conditions once you're enrolled—no exclusions. For international insurance during the visa phase, consider Allianz Care's moratorium underwriting (no medical questions, 2-year pre-existing exclusion) or BUPA's comprehensive underwriting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Japan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Japanese immigration authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
